<dl id="n16048i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n16" href="#n16048i">N16 (VI.D.1)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n16all.htm#n16048i"> 48(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Glewlwyd of the mighty grasp <small>color t.b.a.</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n16048i"> <li>FW39 482.13 </li><li><ms href="#n16048i">MS BL 47484a-253</ms> </li><li>JJA 58:323 <a name="rAd8" href="../../FF/fdra/rda.htm#rAd8">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/rA/rAd8.htm#n16048i">Draft: III&sect;3A.8</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">The winning of Olwen,&mdash;hard enough though it appears in the story, which is mainly concerned with the long series of laborious tasks imposed upon Kulhwch as conditions of gaining her hand&mdash;is made &ldquo;easy&rdquo; through Arthur&apos;s intervention. The hero starts by duly presenting himself at &ldquo;the gate of Arthur&apos;s palace,&rdquo; and he there meets with the porter, <mark>Glewlwyd of the Mighty Grasp</mark>, who conveys to Arthur the news of his arrival. <small> W. Lewis Jones, <a name="WJKA1" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WJKA1"><cite title="source">King Arthur in History and Legend</cite></a> (1914) 46</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: See also <a name="n54125a" href="n54all.htm#n54125a">N54 (VI.B.45):125(a)</a></mm> </dd></dl>
